### User Info API Test
### Base URL
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7092
@authToken = YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Get current logged-in user information (stateless)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/user-info
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 2. Test with invalid token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/user-info
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### 3. Test without authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/user-info

### Examples of expected responses:

### Success Response (200 OK):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "data": {
#     "id": 1,
#     "email": "user@example.com",
#     "username": "username123",
#     "fullname": "John Doe",
#     "phone": "0123456789",
#     "gender": true,
#     "dob": "1995-05-15",
#     "isactive": true,
#     "profilepicture": "https://example.com/avatar.jpg",
#     "isaitested": false,
#     "roleId": 2,
#     "roleName": "User"
#   },
#   "message": "User information retrieved successfully"
# }

### Unauthorized Response (401):
# {
#   "message": "Invalid or missing user ID in token"
# }

### Not Found Response (404):
# {
#   "message": "User not found"
# }

### Forbidden Response (403):
# {
#   "message": "User account is deactivated"
# }

### Error Response (500):
# {
#   "success": false,
#   "message": "An error occurred while retrieving user information",
#   "error": "Detailed error message"
# }